      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEW YORK LIBERTY (1) has a strong record this journey here with two wins and a minor from four starts. Comes off a (20.06) win last time, scoring by 2.25 lengths in a Maiden over 352m at this track. Expected to go close. FEDERAL DEUCE (2) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at Capalaba over 366m behind Hara's Brian (20.72) in a Grade 6. Worth another chance. BONFIRE TEDDY (3) finished in the money two back then was well fancied latest and led into the straight but ran over, finishing third (19.94) at Q Straight in a Grade 6. Has good early speed. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Well placed and gets his chance. SISTER DOLLY (4) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
